The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 January is 164,883 (19,003.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 January, there were 11,807 new confirmed cases (1,360.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 December, there were 11,666 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (141 extra cases).
